The resolver logic is intact, but notice line 175: the `.catch()` **silently swallows every error** — which is exactly why "not working" gives you no signal. The failure is almost certainly one of two things, and they need opposite fixes, so let me not guess. `people.ts` already logs failures to the **background** console, and we can test the People API directly there like we did for Calendar.

Two things to capture:

**1. Check the background console for existing warnings.** Open `chrome://extensions` → Auxilio → "Inspect views: service worker", reproduce (open an event with an unresolved guest), and look for:
```
[auxilio] searchContacts failed <email> Error: People people:searchContacts 403
[auxilio] otherContacts.search failed <email> …
```
A **403** = the access token lacks the contacts scopes (scope/consent problem). No warning at all = the API returned but found no match.

**2. Run this direct probe in the background console** — it separates "scope denied" from "contact genuinely not found":

```js
(async () => {
  const tok = (await chrome.storage.session.get('auxilio.tokens'))['auxilio.tokens'];
  if (!tok) { console.warn('not signed in'); return; }

  // (a) What scopes does the current access token actually carry?
  const info = await (await fetch(
    'https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v3/tokeninfo?access_token=' + tok.accessToken
  )).json();
  console.log('TOKEN SCOPES:', info.scope || info.error);

  // (b) Try a real contacts search for a guest email (replace with one you expect to resolve)
  const email = prompt('Guest email to test contacts lookup:');
  if (!email) return;
  const url = new URL('https://people.googleapis.com/v1/people:searchContacts');
  url.searchParams.set('query', email);
  url.searchParams.set('readMask', 'names,emailAddresses,photos');
  const res = await fetch(url, { headers: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + tok.accessToken } });
  console.log('searchContacts status:', res.status);
  console.log('searchContacts body:', await res.text());
})();
```

What the result tells us:

| Result | Meaning | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `TOKEN SCOPES` is **missing** `contacts.readonly` / `contacts.other.readonly` | You consented before those scopes were added; silent `prompt=none` renew can't widen scope | **Sign out + sign back in** to re-consent (then I can also force-trigger an interactive renew on scope-miss) |
| status **403** (`PERMISSION_DENIED` / People API not enabled) | Scope present but the People API isn't enabled on the OAuth project | Enable People API in the Google Cloud project |
| status **200** but `results` empty | The guest simply isn't in your Google Contacts / "other contacts" | Expected — People API only resolves people you've saved or emailed; not a bug |
| status **200** with a person but the name still doesn't show in the panel | Client-side merge issue | I fix `hooks.ts` |

My leading hypothesis is the **scope row** — you likely first signed in before the contacts scopes existed, and every renew since has been the silent `prompt=none` one (which I just reinforced with `login_hint`), so it never widened scope. If that's it, the proper fix is to **detect a contacts-scope 403 and trigger an interactive re-consent** instead of failing silently — but I want the token-scopes line to confirm before I build that.

Paste the `TOKEN SCOPES:` line and the `searchContacts status` and I'll fix the exact cause.

